22 WHEREAS, in July 2024, Game Warden Austin Powell was presented with the
23 Monty Carmikle Officer of the Year Award at the Arkansas State Game and Fish
24 Commission Enforcement Division's Awards Banquet in Little Rock; and
25
26 WHEREAS, at just twenty-six (26) years old, Powell became one of the
27 youngest game wardens to ever receive this honor; and
28
29 WHEREAS, after playing college baseball at Arkansas State University,
30 Itawamba Community College, Ole Miss, and the University of Arkansas at
31 Monticello, Powell entered into the Arkansas State Game and Fish Commission's
32 Enforcement Cadet School in 2021; and
33
34 WHEREAS, while Powell has been working as a game warden for only four
35 (4) years, he has already made a huge impact on the community through both
36 the cases he has worked and the additional time he has spent spreading his
